.TH NORM_IT "1" "September 2020"
.SH NAME
.BR norm_it " - norm your .c files at 42 School"
.SH SYNOPSYS
.RB bash " norm_it.sh"
.RI [ "OPTIONS" ]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
norm_it is a shell script that help you to norm your .c files and check if they respect the 42's norm.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Display help and exit
.TP
.B -test
Run norminette command only
.TP
.B -all
Run all the norm correction available
.TP
.B -h
Check if 42 Header is present or not and add header if missing
.TP
.B -t
Clean whitespaces at the end of each lines
.TP
.B -i
Correct the indentation
.TP
.B -s
Correct missing space after while/if/for/return if space missing
.TP
.B -e
Replace multiple empty lines by a single one
.TP
.B -v
Correct the aligment of variable declaration in each function
.TP
.B -g
Correct the alignement of the global scope
.SH EXAMPLE
bash norm_it.sh -i -test

It will correct the indentation and check the norm
.SH AUTHOR
Written by Baudoin Haas.
.SH REPORTING BUGS
GNU coreutils online help: <http://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/>

